Managing files and folder permissions

d--directory
- ---file
l ---link
s ----socket
c--charcter device
b ----block device

types of users ---3
1. user
2. Group user
3. other user

permissions are 2 types
1.Alphabet
2.Numeric

read ==4
write ==2 
execute ==1

rwx ==7

In alohabet

user ==u
group user ==G
other user ==O
permission command is chmod.

Example chmod 400 filename
for user all permissions rwx
group user  no permissions
other user no permission

chmod 777 file name
all user all permissions
group user all permissions
other user all permissions

chmod rwxr--r--
all permissions for user
read permission for group uesr
read permission for other user

How to add permissons in alphabet process
 +  =add
 - remove
 = set
 a ==everyone or all

 How to check detail in file permissions 
 getfacl file name

 then owner
 group
 permissions details will be reflect clearly

 Folder permissions change 

 chmod -R file <permission>file name

 Owner change

 EX current owner is root
 new owner is ec2 -user

 chown <root> :<ec2> filename
===================================================
 create user

useradd <new user name>
passwd minimum 8 characters
username and password details will be reflect in etc/passwd folder and /etc/shadow folder

last 10 lines required then command 
tail -n 10 /etc/passwd

top 10 lines required 
head -n 10 /etc/passwd

user name and passwd change also same 
for new user details can be use command getent /etc/passwd
==========================================================================

new user don't have the permission for install or modifiactions anything due to wheel permission not enable hence we can enable wheel group permission through root user 

sudoer etc/sudoers

visudo command giving the permission for wheel
=======================================================================
user modification:

usermod -aG wheel new username

userdel ---for deleting the user

===================================================

loginrestrictions:

usermod -S /sbin/nologin <username> -----nologin or denied permissions
usermod -s /biln/bash  <username >-----------giving permission for user


